= FsTree

VIM Filesystem Tree plugin in Ruby.

Very early alpha but already (somewhat) usable.

== Requirements

VIM Ruby support

== Installation

Copy or link fs_tree* to ~/.vim/plugin (i.e. both the fs_tree directory and the
fs_tree.vim plugin file).

== Usage

:FsTree will open the tree menu.

crsr-left  - close directory (if closed, closes the parent directory)
crsr-right - open directory (and move into it) or file
crsr-up    - navigate up
crsr-down  - navigate down
cr (enter) - toggle (open/close) directory or open file
left-click - toggle (open/close) directory or open file
s          - open a file with split
v          - open a file with vsplit
J          - make a directory the root directory
K          - move the root directory one level up
R          - refresh (currently looses open directory information)

